<TITLE> Pipe gun with bullets recovered at RU hall </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, March 19 (bdnews24.com)  A pipe gun and two rounds of bullets were recovered from Shah Makhdum (SM) Hall of Rajshahi University Wednesday afternoon. "Cleaners discovered the gun and ammunition under the staircase near the main entrance," said Prof Fakir Nazrul Islam, provost of the hall. "They informed the university proctor and the police." Proctor Prof Chowdhury Mohammad Zakaria said security of all residential halls was tightened after the incident. Police arrived and removed the weapon to Motihar Police Station, he said. No case was filed up to afternoon, said Rafiqul Islam, officer-in-charge of Motihar police. Violent clashes between Bangladesh Chhatra League and Ismali Chhatra Shibir shook RU campus most recently on March 13, in which Sharifuzzaman Nomani, general secretary of Shibir's RU unit, was killed. In a previous incident Shibir activists assailed those of Chhatra League on March 11. bdn
